-- Raiffeisen shares dip on cap hike details
-- By Michael Shields
-- Wed Jan 22, 2014 03:07AM EST
-- None



VIENNA, Jan 22 (Reuters) - Shares in Raiffeisen Bank International eased 0.2 percent in early trading after the Austrian lender announced details of a long-awaited capital increase to strengthen its balance sheet and repay state aid. [ID:nL5N0KV3HQ]

The stock was trading at 29.855 euros by 0805 GMT, down from Tuesday's close at 29.90, after RBI said it planned to boost its share capital by half. An accelerated bookbuilding process was due to end later on Wednesday.